+filesystem-safe). The scheduler derives
+`safe_exp = sanitize(experiment_id) + "-" + sha256(experiment_id)[:8]`,
+where `sanitize` replaces any character outside `[A-Za-z0-9._-]` with `_`.
+A bare sanitizer would alias distinct ids (`a/b` and `a_b` both → `a_b`),
+and since pruning matches on the filename prefix that could delete a
+*different* experiment's archives in a shared destination; the raw-id
+hash suffix makes the prefix collision-free. (In the reference deployment
+each experiment already gets its own destination — `DATA_ROOT` defaults to
+`${HOME}/.eden/experiments/${EXPERIMENT_ID}` — so cross-experiment sharing
+is unusual; the hash is defense-in-depth so the safety doesn't *rely* on
+that.)
 
