+8. **Empty repo bundle under Compose (inherited 12b gap).** The export
+   composes the experiment-config text + repo bundle server-side
+   ([`checkpoints.py`](../../reference/packages/eden-wire/src/eden_wire/routers/checkpoints.py));
+   the bundle is built from the task-store-server's `checkpoint_repo_root`
+   (its `--repo-path`). **The compose `task-store-server` service does NOT
+   pass `--repo-path`** (verified — it passes `--artifacts-dir` only), so
+   today *both* manual and auto checkpoints carry an **empty** bundle:
+   wire state round-trips, git history does not. This is a pre-existing
+   12b-portable-checkpoint completeness gap, not introduced here. It is
+   non-trivial to close because there is no single canonical bare repo in
+   the stack — Forgejo is the source of truth and each service keeps its
+   own per-host clone (`orchestrator-repo`, `executor-repo`, …), so the
+   fix needs a design choice (a dedicated checkpoint-repo clone that
+   fetches Forgejo, or bundling directly from Forgejo). **Deferred to a
+   tracked follow-up (§4.2);** auto-checkpoint inherits the gap and its
